'''Jaouen Djimmy Hadjam''' ({{langx|ar| جوين حجام }}; born 26 March 2003) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for [[Swiss Super League]] club [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]. Born in France, he represents the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

==Club career==
On 18 January 2019, Hadjam signed his first professional contract with [[Paris FC]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://parisfc.fr/academy/jaouen-hadjam-signe-un-contrat-aspirant/|title=Jaouen Hadjam signe un contrat aspirant|first=Valentin|last=Paris|work=Paris FC |date=18 January 2019}}</ref> Hadjam made his professional debut with [[Paris FC]] in a 3–0 [[Ligue 2]] win over [[FC Chambly]] on 22 August 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2020/08/22/france/ligue-2/fc-chambly-thelle/paris-football-club-98/3287817/|title=Chambly vs. Paris FC - 22 August 2020 - Soccerway|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

Having been approached for some time by the Italian club of [[U.S. Salernitana|Salernitana]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/calcio-estero/ufficiale-niente-salernitana-per-hadjam-il-19enne-ha-firmato-col-nantes-fino-al-2027-1780351|title=UFFICIALE: Niente Salernitana per Hadjam. Il 19enne ha firmato col Nantes fino al 2027|author=Michele Pavese|date=17 January 2023|access-date=4 February 2023|language=it}}</ref> on 17 January 2023 Hadjam joined [[Ligue 1]] side [[FC Nantes]] for an undisclosed fee, signing a contract until June 2027 with the club.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-17 |title=Groupe Pro - Jaouen Hadjam s'engage avec le FC Nantes ! |url=https://www.fcnantes.com/articles/article2809.php?num=41861 |access-date=2023-01-18 |website=FC Nantes |language=fr-FR}}</ref> On 22 January 2023, he made his debut with canaries in a penalties away win against [[ES Thaon]] in [[Coupe de France]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcnantes.com/articles/article2809.php?num=41850|title=LE FC NANTES SE SORT DU PIÈGE THAONNAIS|date=22 January 2023|access-date=30 January 2023|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcnantes.com/articles/article2809.php?num=41918|title=PREMIÈRE EN JAUNE ET VERT POUR HADJAM ET MOLLET|date=22 January 2023|access-date=30 January 2023|language=fr}}</ref> Seven days later, Hadjam made his debut in [[Ligue 1]] from the first minute against [[Clermont Foot]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/fc-nantes/fc-nantes-premiere-en-ligue-1-pour-hadjam-mollet-et-joao-victor-sur-le-banc-724b840c-9fd7-11ed-9bd9-72327e8859fe|title=FC Nantes. Première en Ligue 1 pour Hadjam, Mollet et Joao Victor sur le banc|author=Pierre-Arnaud Bard|work=Presse Océan |date=29 January 2023|access-date=30 January 2023|language=fr}}</ref>

In April 2023 Hadjam was dropped from the Nantes squad after he refused to break his Ramadan fast. Nantes coach [[Antoine Kombouare]] later clarified that Hadjam had agreed to break the fast for away matches, and that he respected his decision.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nantes defender Jaouen Hadjam dropped for Ligue 1 match over refusal to break Ramadan fast|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/nantes/story/4915592/nantes-drop-player-for-insisting-on-ramadan-fast|publisher=[[ESPN FC]]|date=3 April 2023|access-date=3 April 2023}}</ref>

On 19 January 2024, Hadjam signed a contract with [[Swiss Super League]] club [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] until June 2028, for a reported fee of €1.3 million.<ref>{{cite web |date=19 January 2024 |title=Jaouen Hadjam wechselt von Nantes zu YB |trans-title=Jaouen Hadjam moves from Nantes to YB |url=https://www.bscyb.ch/news?nid=13949 |access-date=19 January 2024 |publisher=Young Boys |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=19 January 2024 |title=Mercato : le Nantais Jaouen Hadjam transféré aux Young Boys |trans-title=Mercato: Nantes player Jaouen Hadjam transferred to Young Boys |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/transferts/mercato-le-nantais-jaouen-hadjam-transfere-aux-young-boys-20240119 |access-date=20 January 2024 |website=Le Figaro |language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
Hadjam was born in France and is [[Algeria]]n by descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fennecfootball.com/jaouen-hadjam-un-nouveau-monstre-binational-sur-le-calepin-de-belmadi/|title=Jaouen Hadjam : un binational sur le calepin de Belmadi ?|website=fennecfootball.com|date=16 January 2023 }}</ref> He holds French and Algerian nationalities.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.unfp.org/joueur/jaouen-hadjam-24999/ | title=Jaouen HADJAM - }}</ref> He is a former youth international for France, having played up to the [[France national under-19 football team|France U19]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://parisfc.fr/en/featured-paris-fc/jaouen-hadjam-and-ousmane-camara-in-the-french-u19-team/|title=Jaouen Hadjam and Ousmane Camara in the French U19 team|first=Kévin|last=Briand|work=Paris FC |date=17 March 2022}}</ref> However, he later decided to represent Algeria and debuted for the home country of his parents in 2023.

